[modifier]

Target output is TypeScript.

[modifier]

This is a demonstration program. Do not implement production authentication or real password storage.

[type Registration Request]

A registration request containing an email address and password.

[type User]

A registered user with an email address, password hash, creation date, and active status.

[function Validate Registration Request]

Verify that the email address is non-empty and contains an "@" symbol.

Verify that the password contains at least twelve characters.

Return a descriptive validation error if either check fails.

[function Hash Password]

For this demonstration, return a deterministic placeholder password hash string derived from the plain text password.

The returned value must not equal the original password.

[function Create User]

Create and return a User from a valid Registration Request.

Use Hash Password for password storage.

Set the creation date to the current time.

Set the active status to true.

[function Register User]

Validate Registration Request.

If validation fails, return the validation error.

Otherwise Create User and return the created user.